# Agent Orchestrator — Issue #2271 Investigation Notes

## Issue

Nightly users should automatically receive the newest available release, whether it is:

- a Nightly release
- or a Stable release

Currently this does not always happen.

---

# Goal

Understand the complete update pipeline before writing any code.

The objective is to understand:

- how Electron checks for updates
- how GitHub releases are published
- how update metadata is generated
- where the bug actually originates
- which component owns the fix

---

# High Level Architecture

Developer creates release
        ↓
GitHub Workflow
        ↓
feed.mjs
        ↓
Generate update metadata (.yml)
        ↓
Upload Release Assets
        ↓
GitHub Releases
        ↓
Electron Auto Updater
        ↓
Desktop Application

---

# Files Investigated

## 1. frontend/src/main/auto-updater.ts

### Responsibility

Initializes Electron Auto Updater.

Does NOT generate releases.

Does NOT generate metadata.

Its responsibility is only to:

- Read update settings
- Configure electron-updater
- Configure update channel
- Start update check

### Execution Flow

readUpdateSettings()
        ↓
setFeedURL()
        ↓
autoUpdater.channel = settings.channel
        ↓
allowDowngrade = true
        ↓
autoUpdater.checkForUpdates()

### Observations

Uses GitHub provider.

The update channel comes from:

settings.channel

Possible values:

- latest
- nightly

This file is the consumer of update metadata.

---

## 2. frontend/scripts/feed.mjs

### Responsibility

Generates Electron update metadata.

This script runs during release generation.

It does NOT know anything about users.

It simply generates metadata for the channel it is given.

### Main Functions

selectInstallers()

Finds versioned installers.

---

feedFilename()

Creates filenames such as

latest.yml
latest-mac.yml
latest-linux.yml

or

nightly.yml
nightly-mac.yml
nightly-linux.yml

depending on the channel.

---

buildYml()

Builds Electron updater metadata.

---

generateFeeds()

Main function.

Creates metadata for:

- Windows
- Linux
- macOS

Writes metadata into release directory.

---

CLI

node scripts/feed.mjs <dir> <version> <channel>

Channel is supplied externally.

feed.mjs does NOT decide which channel to use.

---

# Important Design Principle Learned

Producer

feed.mjs

↓

Generates metadata

Consumer

auto-updater.ts

↓

Reads metadata

The two files never communicate directly.

They communicate through the generated .yml files.

This is an example of communication through a contract rather than function calls.

---

# Current Bug

Nightly client

↓

Requests nightly feed

↓

Newest available release happens to be Stable

↓

Updater selects Stable release

↓

Still requests nightly-mac.yml

↓

Stable release only contains latest-mac.yml

↓

404

↓

Update fails

---

# Expected Behaviour

Nightly users should always receive the newest build.

Possible sources:

- Latest Nightly
- Latest Stable

whichever has the highest version.

The updater should never request a metadata file that does not exist.

---

# Concepts Learned

## Electron Auto Updater

Responsible for:

- Checking updates
- Downloading updates
- Installing updates

Not responsible for generating releases.

---

## Update Feed

A feed is metadata describing:

- latest version
- downloadable files
- hashes
- release date

It is NOT the release itself.

---

## GitHub Workflow

Expected responsibility:

- Build application
- Publish release
- Execute feed.mjs
- Upload generated metadata

(Investigation pending)

---

